FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for `betterme` and remember this specification permanently.

Act as a Senior UI/UX Designer and Front-End Developer.

Create a production-ready application named:

betterme

BASE REPOSITORIES

Use:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/betterme.git

Use ALL wc functionality from:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/blob/main/js/_wc.js

including:

* wc.publish()
* wc.subscribe()
* wc.log()
* wc-include
* all reusable wc utilities

TECH STACK

Use ONLY:

* HTML
* SCSS
* Vanilla JavaScript ES6

Bootstrap 5 is ONLY allowed for:

* layout
* grid utilities

DO NOT USE:

* React
* Vue
* Angular
* jQuery
* external libraries
* inline styles
* inline JavaScript
* IDs
* global CSS
* iframes

MUST USE:

<wc-include href="..." />

APP STRUCTURE

Root element:

<betterme class="betterme"></betterme>

All styles MUST be fully scoped to:

.betterme

Never use global selectors.

CONFIGURATION

Application MUST be fully JSON-driven.

All UI content MUST come from:

betterme.config.js

Do NOT hardcode content in HTML or JavaScript.

JAVASCRIPT

Create a dedicated ES6 class:

MtkBetterme

Initialize automatically inside:

betterme.js

Requirements:

* wait for DOM availability
* support dynamic injection via wc-include
* prevent duplicate initialization
* modular
* reusable
* maintainable
* production-ready

WC EVENT SYSTEM

Subscribe using:

wc.subscribe("4-betterme", this.onMessage.bind(this))

Create:

onMessage(message)

Before every publish:

wc.log(...)

Publish using:

wc.publish(...)

All payloads must be structured and reusable.

DESIGN SYSTEM

Use styles and patterns from:

css/nala.scss

Use Modern Material Design patterns:

* floating labels
* transitions
* motion
* accessibility
* focus states
* responsive layouts
* typography
* spacing
* elevation

ACCESSIBILITY

Application must be:

* ADA compliant
* keyboard accessible
* semantic HTML
* screen-reader friendly
* responsive

Include:

* visible focus states
* proper ARIA usage
* accessible controls

QUIZ EXPERIENCE

The application is a multi-step questionnaire.

QUESTIONS

* 10 questions
* JSON-driven
* each question displayed one at a time
* large bold Arial font
* left aligned
* aligned with answer container

QUESTION IMAGES

Images are located in:

assets/question_1.png
assets/question_2.png
assets/question_3.png
assets/question_4.png
assets/question_5.png
assets/question_6.png
assets/question_7.png
assets/question_8.png
assets/question_9.png
assets/question_10.png

Display image above each question.

Mapping:

question-01 -> question_1.png
question-02 -> question_2.png
question-03 -> question_3.png
question-04 -> question_4.png
question-05 -> question_5.png
question-06 -> question_6.png
question-07 -> question_7.png
question-08 -> question_8.png
question-09 -> question_9.png
question-10 -> question_10.png

Image requirements:

* width: 12rem
* height: auto
* left aligned
* aligned with question and answers
* no borders
* no shadows
* max border radius 5px

THEMES

Support:

* Light Mode
* Dark Mode

Hide the visible "Theme" label.

Keep only theme buttons.

PROGRESS BAR

Progress bar must:

* always remain visible
* fixed to top of viewport
* never disappear during transitions
* height: 20px
* full browser width
* not be inside animated content
* progress updates as questions advance

index.html owns the top offset:

<body style="margin:0;padding:0;padding-top:20px;">

QUIZ TRANSITION

Use:

Fade + Lift

Animation:

* fade in
* slight vertical lift
* smooth easing
* duration: 650ms

Do NOT use:

* horizontal slides
* push transitions
* carousels

ANSWERS

Each answer:

* full width
* single column layout
* stable width during animation
* 2px transparent border

Hover:

* border becomes lime

Selected:

* border becomes lime

Checkbox:

* large checkbox left of answer text
* answer text remains in place
* no layout shift

BUTTONS

Remove:

* Skip button

Keep:

* Previous
* Next

Button requirements:

* width: 180px
* height: 56px minimum
* bold Arial
* large text

Previous button:

‹ Previous

Next button:

Next ›

Chevron requirements:

* large
* prominent
* visually heavier than text

STYLE RULES

Use:

* Arial throughout
* bold question typography
* max border radius: 5px everywhere

Do NOT use:

* rounded pills
* large radii
* shadows around quiz cards

LAYOUT

Quiz card:

* full width
* no max-width shell constraint
* no borders
* no shadows

Answer container:

* max-width: 1280px
* centered

Question:

* left aligned
* same left edge as answers

SUMMARY PAGE

After final question:

Display all questions and answers on a single page.

Summary requirements:

* small text
* 14px
* readable
* printable

OUTPUT

Generate complete files only:

* index.html
* betterme.html
* betterme.js
* betterme.scss
* betterme.config.js

Never generate:

* explanations
* snippets
* partial updates
* markdown code blocks

Always generate complete production-ready files.
